  "text": "While WLI has the potential to identify the interference fringe order from the output pattern of an interferometer [CITATION_1] , it is difficult to distinguish the zero order fringe peak from its adjacent first order fringe peaks when noise is present in the interferometer output, as shown in Figure 3 . From Equations 1 and 2, the amplitude difference ∆I between the zero order fringe peak and the first order fringe peaks is represented as:",
